+# v0.5 ChatGPT Export Import
+
+Date: 2026-06-09
+Phase: ChatGPT export import preview
+Status: PASS for local ChatGPT export import preview
+
+## Goal
+
+Convert ChatGPT export files into local Pala Memory Core records so useful conversations can survive outside the original chat thread.
+
+## Added Behavior
+
+| Area | Change |
+|---|---|
+| CLI | Added `python pala.py import chatgpt-export <path>` |
+| Inputs | `.zip`, folder, `.json`, `.html`, `.md`, `.txt` |
+| ChatGPT JSON | Splits `mapping` conversations into records |
+| Safety | Supports `--max-records` and `--max-chars` |
+| Project link | Supports `--project` |
+| Tags | Adds `chatgpt-export` plus optional user tags |
+
+## Command
+
+```powershell
+python .\pala.py import chatgpt-export export.zip --project trugurpala/pala-memory-core --tag archive
+```
+
+## Expected Result
+
+```text
+saved <record-id>
+data\records\<date>\<record-id>.md
+imported <n> record(s) from <path>
+```
+
+## Smoke Test
+
+Created a sample ChatGPT-style `conversations.json`, zipped it, then imported it:
+
+```powershell
+python .\pala.py import chatgpt-export .\data\inbox\chatgpt-export-sample.zip --project trugurpala/pala-memory-core --tag smoke-test --max-records 3 --max-chars 2000
+python .\pala.py brief today
+python .\pala.py dashboard export
+```
+
+Observed output after BOM-safe JSON decoding fix:
+
+```text
+saved 20260609T132447Z-sample-chatgpt-export-conversation
+data\records\2026-06-09\20260609T132447Z-sample-chatgpt-export-conversation.md
+imported 1 record(s) from C:\Users\Pala-Home-1\Desktop\Codex\pala-memory-core\data\inbox\chatgpt-export-sample.zip
+brief saved data\reports\2026-06-09-brief.md
+dashboard data saved dashboard\records.json
+```
+
+## Release Posture
+
+This is a local import preview. It does not call the ChatGPT service; it reads files the user already has locally.
